query: How do I bake a chocolate cake?
final_response: Here's a simple recipe for a chocolate cake:  Ingredients: - 1 and 3/4 cups (220g) all-purpose flour - 1 and 1/2 teaspoons baking powder - 1 and 1/2 teaspoons baking soda - 3/4 cup (65g) unsweetened cocoa powder - 2 cups (400g) white sugar - 1/2 teaspoon salt - 2 eggs - 1 cup (240ml) whole milk - 1/2 cup (120ml) vegetable oil - 2 teaspoons vanilla extract - 1 cup (240ml) boiling water  Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 175°C (350°F). Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans. 2. In a large bowl, mix together the flour, cocoa, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. 3. Add the eggs, milk, oil, and vanilla extract to the dry ingredients and mix for 2 minutes on medium speed. 4. Stir in the boiling water (the batter will be thin). Pour the batter evenly into the prepared pans. 5. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cakes comes out clean. 6. Allow the cakes to cool in the pans for 10 minutes, then remove from the pans and transfer to a wire rack to cool completely. 7. Once the cakes are cooled, frost with your favorite chocolate frosting and decorate as desired.
